ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Quite a typical graduate seminar, on a topic that does not get discussed enough in undergrad.
I highly recommend this course to any students interested in the study of speciation.
Depends on their interests because it's a pretty specific course. I'd recommend it to anyone who is interested in the topic.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I was familiarized with the literature concerning speciation. This is a topic that I had not investigated with any depth in the past. Learning more about speciation and adaptive radiation allowed me to think about my current project in a different light.
